Hill:
Intermittent social runners
Benefit from targeted internal data and external data
In order to assess and enhance race performance in an engaging manner.

SubHill:
For individual races, if runner chooses to use the application during the race, the runner gets real-time feedback and support with audio notifications while running.

Story:
As an intermittent social runner
I want to get real-time notifications on my performance and specific encouragement/coaching during a race
So that I meet my race goals

Acceptance Criteria:
Given I'm an intermittent social runner who is running a RAM race, and I have preset a goal time for this particular race, and running with a mobile device
When my pace drops below 85% of the avergae pace that I should maintain in order to finish the race within the preset goal 
Then I get audio notification to pace up
